  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Wellbeing of Populations Affected is Strengthened through Camp Coordination and Camp Management (CCCM) Support to IDPs and Host Community.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The displacement context in Ethiopia remains fluid as the country continues to experience conflict and disasters due to natural hazards driven displacements. As the conflict spreads and deepens, it is expected to affect more people and cause further sporadic displacement and increase needs particularly in northern Ethiopia. Through the project, IOM intends to further scale up its ongoing camp coordination and camp management (CCCM) emergency response in the targeted areas and is providing assistance along the four pillars of CCCM with essential protection mainstreaming respecting COVID 19 preventive measures.</narrative>
  </description>
